{"title_page": "Definition (song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Definition\n| cover      = Definition.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Black Star (hip hop group)|Black Star]]\n| album      = [[Mos Def & Talib Kweli Are Black Star]]\n| released   = August 26, 1998\n| format     = [[12-inch single]], [[CD single|CD]], [[Vinyl record|Vinyl]]\n| recorded   = 1997<br>Funky Slice Studios; [[Brooklyn, New York|Brooklyn]], [[New York (state)|NY]]\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Conscious hip hop]]\n| length     = 3:26\n| label      = [[Rawkus Records]]\n| writer     = [[Mos Def|Dante Smith]]<br>[[Talib Kweli|Talib Kweli Greene]]<br>[[Hi-Tek|Tony Cottrell]]\n| producer   = [[Hi-Tek]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Respiration (song)|Respiration]]\n| next_year  = 1999\n}}\n\n'''\"Definition\"''' is the first single from [[Black Star (hip hop group)|Black Star]]'s [[Mos Def & Talib Kweli Are Black Star|eponymously titled]] 1998 album (see [[1998 in music]]). It is produced by [[Hi-Tek]], who [[sampling (music)|samples]] \"The P Is Free\" by [[Boogie Down Productions]] for the track's beat. In addition, the song's chorus [[interpolation (music)|interpolates]] \"Stop the Violence\" by Boogie Down Productions. The chorus and the song's lyrics in general deal with the necessity to stop violence in hip hop. An [[underground hip hop|underground]] hit the song still reached #60 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] chart. It is featured on multiples compilations such as ''[[Best of Decade I: 1995-2005]]'', [[Rawkus Records]]' greatest hits album. [[Allmusic]] writer Jason Kaufman considers it to be a \"flawless\" track.<ref name=\"AMG\">{{cite web | last = Kaufman | first = Jason | url = {{Allmusic|class=album|id=r377081|pure_url=yes}} | title = Black Star Review at Allmusic | format =  | work = | publisher = | accessdate = June 14, 2007}}</ref>\n\nA [[reprise]] of \"Definition\" titled \"RE: DEFinition\" can be found on the ''Black Star'' album.\n\n==Track list==\n\n===A-side===\n# \"Definition\" (Radio Version)\n# \"Definition\" (What We Really Said)\n# \"Definition\" (Instrumental to Your Development)\n\n===B-side===\n# \"Twice Inna Lifetime\" (Radiohead Version)\n# \"Twice Inna Lifetime\" (Streethead Version)\n# \"Twice Inna Lifetime\" (Instrumentally Yours)\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (1998)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n|U.S. ''Billboard'' [[Hot 100]]\n|align=\"center\"|60\n|-\n|U.S. ''Billboard'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Singles & Tracks]]\n|align=\"center\"|31\n|-\n|U.S. ''Billboard'' [[Hot Rap Tracks|Hot Rap Singles]]\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Talib Kweli songs]]\n\n{{Mos Def}}\n{{Talib Kweli}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Definition (Song)}}\n[[Category:1998 singles]]\n[[Category:Protest songs]]\n[[Category:Black Star (group) songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Mos Def]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Talib Kweli]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Hi-Tek]]\n[[Category:1998 songs]]\n[[Category:Rawkus Records singles]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Definition\n| cover      = Definition.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Black Star (hip hop group)|Black Star]]\n| album      = [[Mos Def & Talib Kweli Are Black Star]]\n| released   = May 26, 1998\n| format     = [[12-inch single]], [[CD single|CD]], [[Vinyl record|Vinyl]]\n| recorded   = 1997<br>Funky Slice Studios; [[Brooklyn, New York|Brooklyn]], [[New York (state)|NY]]\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Conscious hip hop]]\n| length     = 3:26\n| label      = [[Rawkus Records]]\n| writer     = [[Mos Def|Dante Smith]]<br>[[Talib Kweli|Talib Kweli Greene]]<br>[[Hi-Tek|Tony Cottrell]]\n| producer   = [[Hi-Tek]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Respiration (song)|Respiration]]\n| next_year  = 1999\n}}\n\n'''\"Definition\"''' is the first single from [[Black Star (hip hop group)|Black Star]]'s [[Mos Def & Talib Kweli Are Black Star|eponymously titled]] 1998 album (see [[1998 in music]]). It is produced by [[Hi-Tek]], who [[sampling (music)|samples]] \"The P Is Free\" by [[Boogie Down Productions]] for the track's beat. In addition, the song's chorus [[interpolation (music)|interpolates]] \"Stop the Violence\" by Boogie Down Productions. The chorus and the song's lyrics in general deal with the necessity to stop violence in hip hop. An [[underground hip hop|underground]] hit the song still reached #60 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] chart. It is featured on multiples compilations such as ''[[Best of Decade I: 1995-2005]]'', [[Rawkus Records]]' greatest hits album. [[Allmusic]] writer Jason Kaufman considers it to be a \"flawless\" track.<ref name=\"AMG\">{{cite web | last = Kaufman | first = Jason | url = {{Allmusic|class=album|id=r377081|pure_url=yes}} | title = Black Star Review at Allmusic | format =  | work = | publisher = | accessdate = June 14, 2007}}</ref>\n\nA [[reprise]] of \"Definition\" titled \"RE: DEFinition\" can be found on the ''Black Star'' album.\n\n==Track list==\n\n===A-side===\n# \"Definition\" (Radio Version)\n# \"Definition\" (What We Really Said)\n# \"Definition\" (Instrumental to Your Development)\n\n===B-side===\n# \"Twice Inna Lifetime\" (Radiohead Version)\n# \"Twice Inna Lifetime\" (Streethead Version)\n# \"Twice Inna Lifetime\" (Instrumentally Yours)\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Chart (1998)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n|U.S. ''Billboard'' [[Hot 100]]\n|align=\"center\"|60\n|-\n|U.S. ''Billboard'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Singles & Tracks]]\n|align=\"center\"|31\n|-\n|U.S. ''Billboard'' [[Hot Rap Tracks|Hot Rap Singles]]\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Talib Kweli songs]]\n\n{{Mos Def}}\n{{Talib Kweli}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Definition (Song)}}\n[[Category:1998 singles]]\n[[Category:Protest songs]]\n[[Category:Black Star (group) songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Mos Def]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Talib Kweli]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Hi-Tek]]\n[[Category:1998 songs]]\n[[Category:Rawkus Records singles]]\n", "name_user": "2601:989:4300:bea0:4997:9e92:4266:547f", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Definition_(song)"}
